"Goodness!
The signs you make..."

902
01:38:33,361 --> 01:38:37,531
they make me crazy about you

903
01:38:39,283 --> 01:38:43,746
What secrets are you exposing...

904
01:38:44,497 --> 01:38:48,918
"what are you telling me
with your eyes?"

905
01:38:49,335 --> 01:38:52,797
You do wield all the magic

906
01:39:29,333 --> 01:39:31,585
Take care of this small car.
It might get lost

907
01:39:34,296 --> 01:39:36,924
Let me tell you again. Whenever
I go to your high society parties...

908
01:39:37,258 --> 01:39:41,053
it ruins my mood. Like my small car
here among big ones...

909
01:39:41,387 --> 01:39:43,973
I will also feel awkward...
small and out of place

910
01:39:44,306 --> 01:39:46,308
"Not again, Raj! Sameer has
invited us with such a lot of love"

911
01:39:46,600 --> 01:39:50,020
"I know, so you can go ahead. I'll go
to Irfan's garage in the neighbourhood"

912
01:39:50,354 --> 01:39:52,356
"Give me a call when the party is
over, I'll come and collect you"

913
01:39:52,606 --> 01:39:55,151
"Raj, does it look nice for me to
go parties alone after my marriage?"

914
01:39:55,484 --> 01:39:59,405
"You're not alone, it's your family,
your friends. What would I do...?"

915
01:40:01,407 --> 01:40:03,284
"Okay, I'm going with you"

916
01:40:13,627 --> 01:40:17,631
"Wow! You look extra beautiful
in that sari! What say, Raj?"

917
01:40:21,343 --> 01:40:23,345
You remember we went to Athens
during our vacations?

918
01:40:26,348 --> 01:40:28,642
"Of course, I remember. Know what, Raj?
There was a lovely lake by the house"

919
01:40:28,976 --> 01:40:31,520
In which Sameer and I went
boating all day

920
01:40:31,854 --> 01:40:36,775
"Remember, Sameer? We insisted with our
parents that we wanted that very house?"

921
01:40:37,276 --> 01:40:41,280
I remember. And I've
fulfilled the condition

922
01:40:41,655 --> 01:40:44,158
"You mean, you...?
- I've bought the house"

923
01:40:47,661 --> 01:40:50,456
You must see that house.
It was beautiful

924
01:40:52,458 --> 01:40:54,543
Why don't you take Raj there
for a holiday?

925
01:40:54,877 --> 01:40:56,879
Lt'll be a break
even for you Raj

926
01:41:11,393 --> 01:41:15,564
You talk about this? How about
the Versace suit you're wearing?

927
01:41:20,444 --> 01:41:23,948
The girl who marries you
is going to be really lucky

928
01:41:32,498 --> 01:41:34,500
What are you guys playing
the boring couple for?

929
01:41:39,505 --> 01:41:41,715
"Must I ask for permission?
Please let me, sir!"

930
01:42:10,744 --> 01:42:14,248
"How's my suit?
- It's nice, sir"

931
01:42:14,748 --> 01:42:16,875
I got it stitched during my wedding

932
01:42:19,753 --> 01:42:22,965
"How about my watch?
- It's nice too, sir"

933
01:42:40,858 --> 01:42:43,152
"Ramji, tell me what price
you're selling ladyfinger for"

934
01:42:43,485 --> 01:42:46,655
10 rupees for a quarter kilo.
- You think we're industrialists?

935
01:42:51,452 --> 01:42:54,455
I hope you liked it Rustom Uncle?
- I loved it

936
01:42:54,788 --> 01:42:56,790
"Your biscuits were nice
too, sister-in-law"

937
01:42:56,957 --> 01:42:59,460
"They were from my shop.
- This is for you, Radha"

938
01:42:59,793 --> 01:43:02,588
Aunt! What a pleasant surprise!

939
01:43:03,505 --> 01:43:05,799
"Do come again, okay?
- Very well. Good bye"

940
01:43:12,806 --> 01:43:14,391
Aunt!

941
01:43:16,810 --> 01:43:19,354
"Tell me what you'll have.
Tea, coffee...?"

942
01:43:19,688 --> 01:43:21,231
I don't want anything

943
01:43:21,607 --> 01:43:24,109
Do these people come
even to your house?

944
01:43:24,693 --> 01:43:27,613
They hadn't seen me in a
long time and came over...

945
01:43:27,946 --> 01:43:31,491
to ask about my well-being.
But tell me how you have been!

946
01:43:31,825 --> 01:43:34,244
"I'm all right.
- Hello, sister-in-law"

947
01:43:34,578 --> 01:43:36,580
How many eggs?
- 6. Keep them in the refrigerator

948
01:43:38,832 --> 01:43:42,502
"Be careful, don't break the eggs.
- Very well, sister-in-law"

949
01:43:43,128 --> 01:43:47,633
"What's happening here, Priya?
Vegetable sellers and egg sellers!"

950
01:43:47,966 --> 01:43:49,968
Are these the only people left
in your life?

951
01:43:50,761 --> 01:43:53,555
"Hello, Lady. Your clothes.
- You got my sari, Ganpat?"

952
01:43:53,889 --> 01:43:56,308
Of course.
- All right. Keep it here

953
01:43:56,642 --> 01:43:58,602
I'll take it in later.
- Very well. Good bye

954
01:43:58,852 --> 01:43:59,853
Good bye

955
01:44:00,437 --> 01:44:03,523
Priya! You even know
your laundryman's name?

956
01:44:04,608 --> 01:44:05,609
"Yes, aunt"

957
01:44:05,984 --> 01:44:08,487
What kind of a life
are you leading?

958
01:44:08,862 --> 01:44:13,492
What have you come to?
And I had such dreams for you

959
01:44:13,867 --> 01:44:17,329
"There's nothing of the sort, aunt.
I'm very happy here"

960
01:44:17,663 --> 01:44:19,665
I'm starting my work
all over again and...

961
01:44:19,873 --> 01:44:23,669
"Raj is landing a new contract too.
- What new contract, Priya"

962
01:44:24,002 --> 01:44:27,923
"I've been hearing that for ages!
Anyway, I've made up my mind"

963
01:44:28,298 --> 01:44:30,550
I've brought you
two tickets to Greece

964
01:44:30,884 --> 01:44:32,886
Go and have a holiday

965
01:44:33,637 --> 01:44:37,015
"But how can I accept it, aunt?
I'm already married"

966
01:44:37,349 --> 01:44:40,227
Why can't you accept it?
I'm like your mother

967
01:44:40,644 --> 01:44:44,356
And a mother can give her daughter
anything and any amount she wants to

968
01:44:44,690 --> 01:44:47,109
You get that? It's her right

969
01:44:51,697 --> 01:44:56,910
"The large-hearted one
will leave with the bride..."

970
01:44:58,954 --> 01:45:02,708
"Raj doesn't like my song and...
- No, Nandu. Go ahead and sing"

971
01:45:03,041 --> 01:45:07,921
Can I? Even in the night?
- You may sing all night

972
01:45:09,631 --> 01:45:12,592
So I'm going to sing
for Raj tonight!

973
01:45:12,926 --> 01:45:17,264
"Raj, you sing so well too.
Join me in the nights"

974
01:45:17,723 --> 01:45:21,351
"I'm all alone.
- Some other time, Nandu"

975
01:45:21,685 --> 01:45:23,687
"Tonight, I have a programme
for romance"

976
01:45:24,020 --> 01:45:25,021
Really?

977
01:45:26,022 --> 01:45:28,734
You provide the background music
and I'll get on with the romance

978
01:45:36,950 --> 01:45:38,952
Is this Mr Raj Mathur's house?

979
01:45:40,036 --> 01:45:43,081
"Yes, but he's not in right now"

980
01:45:44,750 --> 01:45:48,295
What's the hurry? It's wonderful
that Raj Mathur is not at home

981
01:45:48,962 --> 01:45:51,298
Let me shut the door...
- You?

982
01:45:51,673 --> 01:45:55,635
I'm your immediate neighbour.
The building opposite yours...

983
01:45:55,969 --> 01:46:00,223
"third floor, third window.
- Oh yes, I've seen you"

984
01:46:00,557 --> 01:46:02,309
And I saw you watching

985
01:46:03,685 --> 01:46:07,314
Know what? I've been waiting
for this opportunity for many days

986
01:46:07,939 --> 01:46:09,983
Frankly speaking... so was I

987
01:46:14,488 --> 01:46:16,990
"What do you mean by "so was l"?
What...?"

988
01:46:17,324 --> 01:46:18,658
I'll explain

989
01:46:18,992 --> 01:46:20,994
What are you doing?
- Taking advantage

990
01:46:21,328 --> 01:46:23,788
What advantage?
- He hasn't any time from his trucks

991
01:46:24,122 --> 01:46:27,083
Lay off! Doesn't he have
to work and make money?

992
01:46:27,417 --> 01:46:30,587
Let him make money. You come inside.
- With a stranger...

993
01:46:31,004 --> 01:46:33,215
"What's all this, Priya?
You're kidding, aren't you?"

994
01:46:34,966 --> 01:46:36,009
Mr Neighbour!

995
01:46:36,343 --> 01:46:39,804
I've never seen you
in this light before

996
01:46:40,138 --> 01:46:42,807
"I'm very happy today, Raj.
- Always be happy"

997
01:46:43,141 --> 01:46:45,018
But not with the neighbour

998
01:46:45,810 --> 01:46:47,771
I've got to give you 2 bits
of good news

999
01:46:48,021 --> 01:46:50,023
Give me the second one first

1000
01:46:50,565 --> 01:46:53,360
"Remember, I sent my designs
to an Australian company?"

1001
01:46:54,027 --> 01:46:55,570
They've approved

1002
01:46:56,821 --> 01:46:58,823
And listen to the second
good news

1003
01:47:00,742 --> 01:47:02,744
Tickets for Greece. Look

1004
01:47:05,580 --> 01:47:10,043
Tickets for Greece?
You've won a jackpot?

1005
01:47:11,044 --> 01:47:13,296
Aunt Anna gifted it to us

1006
01:47:14,839 --> 01:47:16,049
Aunt Anna?

1007
01:47:17,175 --> 01:47:21,221
"Since we haven't been on a honeymoon,
she asked us to visit Greece, Raj"

1008
01:47:25,976 --> 01:47:29,604
What happened?
- Well... one second

1009
01:47:30,188 --> 01:47:32,065
What happened?
- One second

1010
01:47:32,607 --> 01:47:35,485
"Nothing.
- What happened, Raj? Tell me"

1011
01:47:36,861 --> 01:47:38,822
"Priya, if you don't mind,
let me tell you something"

1012
01:47:39,072 --> 01:47:43,493
"We'll surely go to Greece,
but with our own money, okay?"

1013
01:47:43,827 --> 01:47:46,746
"But this is our money too.
- No, it isn't our money"

1014
01:47:47,080 --> 01:47:49,749
It's Aunt Anna's money.
- But aunt's like our mother too

1015
01:47:50,083 --> 01:47:54,087
"No, Priya. For you, she is.
Not for me"

1016
01:47:55,088 --> 01:47:57,382
Why're you making a prestige
issue out of this?

1017
01:47:57,716 --> 01:48:01,678
"C'mon, Priya! It hasn't to do
with prestige, honestly"

1018
01:48:02,095 --> 01:48:05,765
So what is it?
- What is it?

1019
01:48:07,100 --> 01:48:09,561
I'll tell you what it is

1020
01:48:09,894 --> 01:48:12,480
I've always got the feeling
that your folks...

1021
01:48:12,814 --> 01:48:15,900
are not very happy with our marriage.
That's how I feel

1022
01:48:16,234 --> 01:48:19,070
They probably think that if you
had got married to Sameer...

1023
01:48:19,404 --> 01:48:22,574
he could have given you everything
that I haven't been able to

1024
01:48:22,907 --> 01:48:25,201
And that's right too. There's
no question of prestige at all

1025
01:48:25,535 --> 01:48:28,329
"Raj, I think you haven't been able
to understand me at all"

1026
01:48:28,705 --> 01:48:30,707
Did I ever say anything
in this regard to you?

1027
01:48:30,874 --> 01:48:31,875
No.
- Did I ever complain?

1028
01:48:32,167 --> 01:48:35,295
So why must you misunderstand?
- Don't raise your voice!

1029
01:48:36,421 --> 01:48:38,423
You're the one who doesn't
get it right

1030
01:48:40,008 --> 01:48:41,926
You are the one they want
to send away on a holiday

1031
01:48:42,135 --> 01:48:43,845
You are the one they pity

1032
01:48:44,137 --> 01:48:46,139
You are the one they want to
see happy... not me or us

1033
01:48:46,598 --> 01:48:50,268
They've got to tolerate me because
I am unfortunately their son-in-law!

1034
01:48:55,148 --> 01:48:57,150
I don't know why you
take things to such limits!

1035
01:48:57,484 --> 01:48:59,569
You think of things
that make no sense!

1036
01:48:59,903 --> 01:49:03,823
Makes no sense?
For you it must be senseless

1037
01:49:04,157 --> 01:49:07,869
"For me, it's a truth
I feel every day..."

1038
01:49:15,293 --> 01:49:17,337
"May we end this discussion here?
- Yes, please!"

1039
01:49:24,177 --> 01:49:25,970
Are you going to sleep?

1040
01:49:45,990 --> 01:49:49,619
"Trouble with Priya again?
- No, no trouble with Priya"

1041
01:49:49,994 --> 01:49:52,664
"No, you do have trouble with her.
- Okay, okay"

1042
01:49:52,997 --> 01:49:56,334
"Last night, I had another
argument with Priya. Happy?"

1043
01:49:56,668 --> 01:49:59,546
Happy my foot!
Now listen to me

1044
01:49:59,963 --> 01:50:03,550
"When we buy a new truck, we have
a few problems initially, don't we?"

1045
01:50:03,883 --> 01:50:05,885
What are you talking about?
- Hear me out first!

1046
01:50:06,219 --> 01:50:08,680
"A new truck also stalls
when it heats up, doesn't it?"

1047
01:50:09,013 --> 01:50:10,848
"All right, it does.
- So what do we do?"

1048
01:50:11,015 --> 01:50:13,017
Don't we shut it down
and start it again?

1049
01:50:13,226 --> 01:50:15,895
So there's not much difference
between a truck and marriage

1050
01:50:16,229 --> 01:50:19,023
They ask for a bit of adjustment
which you've got to make...

1051
01:50:19,357 --> 01:50:22,902
and carry the story further. Right?
- How does one take it further?

1052
01:50:23,987 --> 01:50:26,906
Silly arguments! Are marriages
and trucks like each other?

1053
01:50:27,240 --> 01:50:29,701
Isn't it her fault too?
- Now get one thing clearly

1054
01:50:30,034 --> 01:50:32,912
"Between man and wife, never try to
find out who's right and who's wrong"

1055
01:50:33,246 --> 01:50:35,707
Just say sorry and finish
the matter there and then

1056
01:50:36,040 --> 01:50:39,669
That's what I always do.
- I'm prepared to say sorry too

1057
01:50:40,044 --> 01:50:43,256
"I don't like fighting,
I don't want to fight"

1058
01:50:43,840 --> 01:50:46,217
"But the same rule applies
to her also, doesn't it?"

1059
01:50:46,551 --> 01:50:50,972
"Now look, now don't split hair.
I know the problems with you"

1060
01:50:51,389 --> 01:50:54,392
What's my problem? What?
- Want me start counting?

1061
01:50:56,269 --> 01:50:59,522
"I know, Manubhai. There are
problems with me too"

1062
01:51:00,023 --> 01:51:03,276
That's exactly why I am asking
you to take my advise

1063
01:51:04,444 --> 01:51:07,947
"What am I to do, Manubhai?
- Go to Priya today..."

1064
01:51:08,281 --> 01:51:10,867
like the perfect husband.
The ideal husband

1065
01:51:13,202 --> 01:51:15,288
Ideal?
- Like me

1066
01:51:17,582 --> 01:51:19,417
Is it funny?

1067
01:51:31,304 --> 01:51:35,892
"Priya, I got this gourd,
ladyfinger, carrot..."

1068
01:51:36,309 --> 01:51:41,314
and other stuff from the vendor.
And this one too

1069
01:51:43,316 --> 01:51:47,612
I'll put all this in
the refrigerator

1070
01:51:48,321 --> 01:51:49,989
That is where it is kept

1071
01:51:50,323 --> 01:51:52,658
I bought it all
from the wholesale shop

1072
01:51:53,201 --> 01:51:56,329
The vendor there took me for a fool

1073
01:51:57,121 --> 01:51:59,749
"I asked him for the price of carrots
and he says "30 rupees for a kilo"

1074
01:52:00,041 --> 01:52:04,003
"I asked him to give it at 20 rupees,
or I was leaving"

1075
01:52:05,129 --> 01:52:06,923
He gave it to me at once

1076
01:52:08,132 --> 01:52:10,343
How much would you buy it for?
- 10 rupees a kilo

1077
01:52:16,140 --> 01:52:19,685
But this is fresh... and red

1078
01:52:25,358 --> 01:52:28,611
"If there are any chores to
be done, just tell me"

1079
01:52:34,325 --> 01:52:38,162
I'll wash these utensils.
I'm in the mood today

1080
01:52:40,164 --> 01:52:44,544
I forgot to tell you about the office.
Manubhai came calling today

1081
01:52:45,169 --> 01:52:47,171
He had a cup of tea
and went his way

1082
01:52:49,257 --> 01:52:52,051
Mohammadbhai also came calling.
He had a cup of tea and...

1083
01:52:52,385 --> 01:52:54,887
he went his way too

1084
01:52:57,390 --> 01:53:01,811
And then came Vivek.
He asked me for two trucks

1085
01:53:02,144 --> 01:53:05,064
"I said I didn't have two trucks,
they're away for servicing"

1086
01:53:05,398 --> 01:53:08,609
"One had an axle broken,
another's bonnet wouldn't open"

1087
01:53:08,943 --> 01:53:12,280
"And I said, I couldn't
give him the trucks"

1088
01:53:12,613 --> 01:53:14,532
I asked him to have a cup of tea...
and go his way

1089
01:53:16,576 --> 01:53:18,411
He went his way too

1090
01:53:19,370 --> 01:53:21,956
Everybody went his way
at the office today

1091
01:53:26,168 --> 01:53:30,423
Where do I keep these utensils?
- Keep it where you picked it up from

1092
01:53:32,091 --> 01:53:34,427
But here...
- They're washed utensils

1093
01:53:37,179 --> 01:53:38,973
I washed them

1094
01:53:39,432 --> 01:53:41,642
So I washed them again!

1095
01:53:42,310 --> 01:53:44,437
These big vessels
get dirty very soon

1096
01:53:44,770 --> 01:53:46,772
One must wash them
as often as one can

1097
01:53:48,274 --> 01:53:52,111
Look at this one...
gleaming!

1098
01:53:52,445 --> 01:53:58,117
"Raj, I know what you're trying to say.
But you needn't do all this"

1099
01:53:58,451 --> 01:54:01,454
That you realise it
is enough for me

1100
01:54:06,459 --> 01:54:08,794
"Go and sit down. Let me warm the food.
- No, we're having carrot halwa"

1101
01:54:09,128 --> 01:54:11,047
with our dinner tonight.
And I'm making it.

1102
01:54:11,380 --> 01:54:14,925
Can you?
- But I'll keep trying till you hug me

1103
01:54:15,301 --> 01:54:18,471
And what's so great about carrot
halwa? Grate a bit of carrot and...

1104
01:54:19,263 --> 01:54:20,890
Does it hurt?

1105
01:54:27,229 --> 01:54:29,815
Know what Priya?
It isn't that finger...

1106
01:54:30,483 --> 01:54:32,485
this is the one I nicked

1107
01:54:32,985 --> 01:54:34,987
I've cut my finger.
Please give me a hug!

1108
01:54:46,290 --> 01:54:47,333
How are you doing?

1109
01:54:47,666 --> 01:54:49,668
"Manubhai, coming for
a cup of tea?"

1110
01:54:51,962 --> 01:54:54,298
"Good morning, my foot!
Have you read the newspapers?"

1111
01:54:54,632 --> 01:54:57,635
Why? Has news of your fight with
your wife been printed in it?

1112
01:55:02,264 --> 01:55:05,184
Look at this.
The company you worked for...

1113
01:55:05,518 --> 01:55:07,520
has closed down overnight.
It has gone bust

1114
01:55:09,522 --> 01:55:11,524
What are you talking about?
- Read it

1115
01:55:13,317 --> 01:55:15,444
"Yes, Raj.
We're in serious trouble"

1116
01:55:15,778 --> 01:55:18,322
The bankers called thrice.
They want to see you

1117
01:55:48,018 --> 01:55:50,980
How will he be able to repay
2.5 million in a single week?

1118
01:55:51,355 --> 01:55:53,232
I can't do anything about that

1119
01:55:53,566 --> 01:55:57,361
"Mr Mathur, if the bank is not
repaid its dues in a week..."

1120
01:55:57,695 --> 01:56:00,573
we'll have to seize
all your properties

1121
01:56:45,701 --> 01:56:48,287
"Raj, where have you been
all this while?"

1122
01:56:48,621 --> 01:56:52,041
I've told you so often to telephone me
if you're going to be late

1123
01:56:52,374 --> 01:56:54,376
Your telephone in the office
wasn't reachable

1124
01:56:54,627 --> 01:56:57,713
I spoke to Vivek and Deepak. Even
they didn't know where you were

1125
01:56:58,422 --> 01:57:01,634
"You know how worried
I get for you, Raj"

1126
01:57:09,308 --> 01:57:10,976
What is the matter?

1127
01:57:11,435 --> 01:57:13,103
"What is it, Raj?"

1128
01:57:13,687 --> 01:57:15,648
Tell me what happened

1129
01:57:17,566 --> 01:57:20,652
The company we have most of
our business dealings with...

1130
01:57:21,445 --> 01:57:25,449
has gone bankrupt. With that
goes the money they owed us

1131
01:57:28,452 --> 01:57:29,536
You mean...?

1132
01:57:29,870 --> 01:57:33,665
I have bank loans and other
debts to repay...

1133
01:57:35,667 --> 01:57:37,669
I don't know what to do

1134
01:57:38,879 --> 01:57:42,424
Don't be upset. Come and
eat something first. Come on

1135
01:57:42,800 --> 01:57:43,759
No

1136
01:57:47,429 --> 01:57:49,681
Do you want me to
have a word with Papa?

1137
01:57:51,725 --> 01:57:53,018
"No, Priya"

1138
01:57:55,479 --> 01:57:58,399
Every decision I have taken in life
has been my very own

1139
01:57:59,691 --> 01:58:01,693
I never sought any help

1140
01:58:02,486 --> 01:58:07,282
"And from this difficult situation,
we will have to find our way out"

1141
01:58:13,580 --> 01:58:18,043
"Don't lose hope, Raj.
The two of us will think of a way"

1142
01:58:18,502 --> 01:58:23,715
"You have your Friend with you.
You have faith in Him, don't you?"

1143
01:58:24,508 --> 01:58:26,343
He will help us

1144
01:58:42,693 --> 01:58:45,737
I expected business from your
company and took an extra loan...

1145
01:58:45,863 --> 01:58:49,158
"for two trucks, sir...
- You're getting so worked up..."

1146
01:58:49,741 --> 01:58:52,744
as if it's not my company
but yours that has sunk

1147
01:58:54,246 --> 01:58:59,168
"Actually, sir, there is lot of
money your company owes me"

1148
01:58:59,251 --> 01:59:02,421
"No, no... the company
owes you nothing"

1149
01:59:02,754 --> 01:59:07,759
"It "owed" you money. Past tense.
Because the company is no more"

1150
01:59:09,761 --> 01:59:12,347
"But I did my work with
all honesty, sir..."

1151
01:59:12,890 --> 01:59:16,768
Why did you?
Did I ask you to be honest?

1152
01:59:17,311 --> 01:59:22,190
Look at me! My company has sunk!
But have I sunk? No

1153
01:59:22,357 --> 01:59:24,192
Learn something

1154
01:59:24,776 --> 01:59:29,197
"I'm no match for you, sir.
All I want..."

1155
01:59:29,531 --> 01:59:34,453
Now don't bother me. I'm going
away to Europe for two months

1156
01:59:34,912 --> 01:59:37,456
I'm very tired.
I want to relax

1157
01:59:39,791 --> 01:59:44,212
"But yes, I'm thinking of starting
a new company after I return"

1158
01:59:44,796 --> 01:59:47,799
You can meet me then.
I'll do something for you

1159
01:59:48,050 --> 01:59:50,218
"In the meantime, you can
take a holiday too"

1160
01:59:50,385 --> 01:59:53,221
Where do you folks go?
What do you call that place...?

1161
01:59:53,347 --> 01:59:57,809
"Khandala...? Go to Khandala.
- Thank you, sir..."

1162
01:59:59,019 --> 02:00:03,231
but I don't want to go anywhere.
It's just that by the time you return...

1163
02:00:03,815 --> 02:00:05,567
the time the bank has given me
will be over

1164
02:00:05,817 --> 02:00:09,821
You're ruining my time
and my mood now

1165
02:00:11,448 --> 02:00:14,826
There are many people like you who
are upset at the company going bust

1166
02:00:15,118 --> 02:00:19,831
And I haven't started a charity to
distribute alms to everyone coming here!

1167
02:00:20,832 --> 02:00:23,835
"I'm not asking for alms, sir.
I'm asking for my rights"

1168
02:00:24,336 --> 02:00:30,509
Rights? You don't ask for rights!
You only ask for alms

1169
02:00:30,801 --> 02:00:33,845
"If you want your rights,
go to the courts"

1170
02:01:05,168 --> 02:01:08,880
"Raj, have this coffee.
And change your clothes quickly"

1171
02:01:17,556 --> 02:01:19,099
"What is the matter, Raj?"

1172
02:01:24,146 --> 02:01:25,897
"What happened, Raj?"

1173
02:01:28,900 --> 02:01:30,902
I... I just felt like crying

1174
02:02:02,934 --> 02:02:06,354
"Nothing's working, Manubhai.
I've tried everything"

1175
02:02:06,938 --> 02:02:08,940
We'll have to sell the trucks

1176
02:02:10,442 --> 02:02:13,361
Everything's going to go away.
- No way

1177
02:02:13,445 --> 02:02:16,948
I'll telephone Jignesh right away.
- Why keep calling Jignesh!

1178
02:02:17,073 --> 02:02:20,368
How many people will you talk to?
You spoke to... Saeed earlier

1179
02:02:20,952 --> 02:02:22,954
Did he give you any money?
Nobody's going to

1180
02:02:23,455 --> 02:02:26,583
You've given me so much already.
This chap is cancelling his wedding

1181
02:02:26,958 --> 02:02:29,961
"Everybody's trying his best,
but nothing's happening. Nothing"

1182
02:02:30,086 --> 02:02:34,966
"Look, have patience. Ups and downs
are part of business. Right?"

1183
02:02:35,091 --> 02:02:38,970
"Oh yes, don't lose hope, Raj.
We'll find a way out"

1184
02:02:39,095 --> 02:02:40,972
What way will we find...? What?

1185
02:02:41,139 --> 02:02:44,392
Someone else's company closes down
and the bank holds me by the throat!

1186
02:02:44,476 --> 02:02:45,977
Let me try

1187
02:02:47,187 --> 02:02:50,982
There's another notice from the bank.
- What new notice is this?

1188
02:02:51,274 --> 02:02:54,402
"It says, you've got to 3.5 million,
not 2.5"

1189
02:02:54,986 --> 02:02:59,407
3.5 million? How come?
I've settled it at 2.5 with the bank!

1190
02:02:59,658 --> 02:03:01,993
"Look at how the bankers
are behaving, Manubhai"

1191
02:03:02,160 --> 02:03:04,412
I had a clear understanding
with them that...

1192
02:03:08,416 --> 02:03:11,002
This is a cheque. For 2.5 million

1193
02:03:13,630 --> 02:03:16,424
It's yours.
- Ours

1194
02:03:16,800 --> 02:03:19,427
Don't worry. I haven't taken it
from Papa. I swear

1195
02:03:20,011 --> 02:03:22,430
Remember my assignment
from the Australian company?

1196
02:03:24,015 --> 02:03:26,184
It has been approved.
And this is the advance

1197
02:03:27,185 --> 02:03:31,439
"But who'd give 2.5 as an advance...?
- Big folks, big business"

1198
02:03:32,023 --> 02:03:35,026
They have hefty advances too.
They aren't beggars like us

1199
02:03:36,152 --> 02:03:39,030
You can have the money.
I'll manage on credit

1200
02:03:41,700 --> 02:03:44,452
"What a narrow escape! Else,
we'd have lost this office too..."

1201
02:03:44,536 --> 02:03:47,455
and we'd sit under the
staircase with our accounts

1202
02:03:53,461 --> 02:03:56,464
"Manubhai, don't drink too much.
- This is my first drink!"

1203
02:03:59,050 --> 02:04:01,469
This is the photograph Raj had
torn up in a fit of emotions

1204
02:04:07,058 --> 02:04:09,060
Why're you roaming around
with the photo?

1205
02:04:10,061 --> 02:04:15,483
I've had to work so hard for Priya...
and the photo's damaged anyway

1206
02:04:28,079 --> 02:04:31,082
"What are you upto, Raj?
What will Priya think?"

1207
02:04:31,583 --> 02:04:34,502
It's Priya I'm doing it too.
- I see. Go ahead

1208
02:04:36,087 --> 02:04:39,090
"Know what, Manubhai? I'll telephone
Sameer and call him over"

1209
02:04:39,257 --> 02:04:42,510
"All right... who's that?
- Her friend from Europe, remember?"

1210
02:04:42,719 --> 02:04:46,097
"No, he'll find it odd here!
- He'll talk to her..."

1211
02:04:46,431 --> 02:04:49,100
"and she'll be happy. Else,
we keep talking only about the garage"

1212
02:04:50,101 --> 02:04:52,520
"Sameer, this is Raj here.
Where are you?"

1213
02:04:53,104 --> 02:04:56,524
You're so close to our house!
Come over

1214
02:04:58,109 --> 02:05:01,112
"We're having a party,
a small get-together..."

1215
02:05:01,237 --> 02:05:03,531
come over. Priya's here too

1216
02:05:04,782 --> 02:05:06,117
Talk to her

1217
02:05:10,246 --> 02:05:13,541
It's Sameer. I've called him over

1218
02:05:18,129 --> 02:05:21,132
"No, it's a small get-together.
- One moment"

1219
02:05:22,133 --> 02:05:24,552
"Sameer, Priya's busy
for a second"

1220
02:05:28,556 --> 02:05:31,142
"Yes, Sameer. Talk to her"

1221
02:05:35,438 --> 02:05:37,148
Raj insists that you must come

1222
02:05:40,151 --> 02:05:42,654
"And listen, I'm talking to you
from another room now"

1223
02:05:43,571 --> 02:05:46,574
Don't even make the mistake of
telling Raj...

1224
02:05:46,658 --> 02:05:48,576
that you're the one I took
the money from

1225
02:05:49,160 --> 02:05:51,913
"It should remain between
you and me, Sameer"

1226
02:05:54,457 --> 02:05:56,459
Raj mustn't get to know

1227
02:06:10,598 --> 02:06:12,350
I've been talking to Sameer

1228
02:06:16,688 --> 02:06:18,189
"Is there anything you want, Raj?"

1229
02:06:20,650 --> 02:06:21,693
No

1230
02:06:28,199 --> 02:06:30,618
So Sameer was the one
who gave you the money?

1231
02:06:33,204 --> 02:06:36,624
Just tell me whether Sameer
gave you the money or not

1232
02:06:37,875 --> 02:06:40,211
"Raj, I...
- Yes, or no!"

1233
02:06:42,213 --> 02:06:43,214
Yes

1234
02:06:43,631 --> 02:06:46,384
Why did you take the money from Sameer?
- Raj...

1235
02:06:46,551 --> 02:06:49,220
Why did you take it from Sameer?
- Talk softly

1236
02:06:49,387 --> 02:06:52,640
We have guests at home.
We'll end up having a drama...

1237
02:06:52,849 --> 02:06:56,227
But we're already part of a drama!
You're worried about the guests?

1238
02:06:56,519 --> 02:06:59,647
I'll show you what a drama is!

1239
02:07:03,234 --> 02:07:06,237
Thanks for coming to the party.
Shut that music!

1240
02:07:08,948 --> 02:07:10,867
Go home. This moment!

1241
02:07:13,911 --> 02:07:15,246
I'm not kidding!

1242
02:07:16,539 --> 02:07:17,832
Go away!
- It's only 10

1243
02:07:17,874 --> 02:07:21,252
The party at my house is
over at 10. Get going!

1244
02:07:23,254 --> 02:07:26,257
What's gotten into you?
- I'm sorry

1245
02:07:26,674 --> 02:07:29,677
"Before I get nastier, go away.
- All right"

1246
02:07:42,398 --> 02:07:44,275
"The drama is over, okay?"

1247
02:07:44,609 --> 02:07:48,279
"Now tell me, why did you
take the money from Sameer?"

1248
02:07:49,572 --> 02:07:52,909
"You had a bank loan to repay...
you were so upset, Raj"

1249
02:07:53,284 --> 02:07:55,453
And so you took the money
from Sameer?

1250
02:07:56,078 --> 02:07:58,289
"You didn't sleep all nights, Raj."

1251
02:07:58,581 --> 02:08:02,710
Now I won't sleep all my life!
You took money from Sameer!

1252
02:08:03,294 --> 02:08:05,713
What would be the worst
thing to happen? What?

1253
02:08:06,005 --> 02:08:09,300
"Our business would have wound up,
this house would have been sold..."

1254
02:08:09,425 --> 02:08:12,720
and we'd have been out on the streets.
But there are millions on the streets!

1255
02:08:12,929 --> 02:08:16,307
"Their life is a struggle, but
they have faith in each other"

1256
02:08:16,641 --> 02:08:19,727
"They trust each other.
- I tried everywhere, Raj"

1257
02:08:20,436 --> 02:08:22,813
I even spoke to the export company

1258
02:08:23,314 --> 02:08:26,108
"But when they didn't give me
any money, I asked Sameer..."

1259
02:08:26,317 --> 02:08:28,319
I didn't take a penny
from my own father!

1260
02:08:28,819 --> 02:08:31,447
"I didn't borrow from my relatives,
not even from your father!"

1261
02:08:31,739 --> 02:08:35,743
And you went and begged Sameer?
What will he think?

1262
02:08:36,327 --> 02:08:42,750
That it's because of his favours
that I'm so happy and delighted!

1263
02:08:42,875 --> 02:08:45,753
"It's no favour, Raj.
It's business"

1264
02:08:45,962 --> 02:08:48,339
"I've got to make garments for him, Raj.
I've only taken an advance"

1265
02:08:50,758 --> 02:08:53,135
Are you going to
teach me business now?

1266
02:08:54,762 --> 02:08:58,766
Does anyone give such a big advance?
And you know why he gave the advance!

1267
02:08:58,891 --> 02:09:01,352
"You know it and I know it,
you will not say it..."

1268
02:09:01,686 --> 02:09:04,772
But I'll tell you!
He gave you the advance...

1269
02:09:04,897 --> 02:09:07,358
because he's still in love with you.
- Raj!

1270
02:09:08,484 --> 02:09:10,361
And you know that he's
in love with you!

1271
02:09:10,486 --> 02:09:11,988
Which is why he gave the money

1272
02:09:14,031 --> 02:09:16,367
You know he loves you
and gave you the money

1273
02:09:16,659 --> 02:09:18,786
Does anyone give such a huge
advance just like that?

1274
02:09:26,794 --> 02:09:29,797
"Priya, Sameer's here.
Welcome, Sameer"

1275
02:09:30,381 --> 02:09:33,801
You're the one we were waiting for.
We were talking about you

1276
02:09:35,386 --> 02:09:38,806
It's your house...
he has brought you flowers!

1277
02:09:40,683 --> 02:09:43,811
"Sorry, I've broken all the bottles.
- What is the matter, Priya?"

1278
02:09:43,894 --> 02:09:45,813
I'll tell you what the matter is

1279
02:09:46,397 --> 02:09:49,817
The truth is that the two of you
have made a fool out of me

1280
02:09:50,401 --> 02:09:53,404
All I want to know is
why you did it?

1281
02:09:53,571 --> 02:09:57,533
"It's between you and me, Raj. Why
are you dragging Sameer into it?"

1282
02:09:57,700 --> 02:10:02,830
"Don't stand up for Sameer!
Don't... okay, okay, I'm sorry"

1283
02:10:03,122 --> 02:10:06,834
"Do stand up for him! Go ahead!
You're made for each other, right?"

1284
02:10:08,044 --> 02:10:11,130
"She's wearing such a lovely sari,
and look at your suit..."

1285
02:10:11,422 --> 02:10:12,840
Which suit is this?

1286
02:10:13,424 --> 02:10:15,843
"I'm not fighting, I'm only
taking a look at the suit"

1287
02:10:16,427 --> 02:10:18,429
Don't touch me! I'm taking
a look at his suit!

1288
02:10:28,439 --> 02:10:29,940
"What are you talking about, Raj?"

1289
02:10:35,738 --> 02:10:38,866
I've got nothing. You've got the money!
It's aunt who sends tickets for me

1290
02:10:39,450 --> 02:10:42,453
And your dream of childhood
in Switzerland...

1291
02:10:48,459 --> 02:10:50,878
And there's Sameer
to lend us money

1292
02:10:52,713 --> 02:10:54,882
This is between the two of you.
I must leave

1293
02:10:54,965 --> 02:10:57,885
Where d'you think you're going?
It's between the two of you!

1294
02:10:57,968 --> 02:11:00,137
Rather I go away!

1295
02:11:01,472 --> 02:11:04,892
"Actually, I'll call a priest and
have the two of you married"

1296
02:11:06,227 --> 02:11:08,896
"Why even call a priest? I know
the rites, I was recently married"

1297
02:11:08,979 --> 02:11:11,482
I remember everything.
Give me your hand...

1298
02:11:12,483 --> 02:11:13,901
"What are you up to, Raj?"

1299
02:11:57,528 --> 02:12:00,531
I'm in love...

1300
02:12:01,532 --> 02:12:04,535
you are in love...

1301
02:12:05,202 --> 02:12:09,957
so what have things come to be?

1302
02:12:12,710 --> 02:12:15,796
I am not unfaithful...

1303
02:12:16,547 --> 02:12:19,550
you are not unfaithful...

1304
02:12:20,217 --> 02:12:25,973
"so why do we hold
so much against each other?"

1305
02:12:28,142 --> 02:12:32,980
We were walking together...

1306
02:12:35,190 --> 02:12:39,987
"so what caused these
distances between us?"

1307
02:12:46,076 --> 02:12:48,996
We don't even know...

1308
02:12:50,581 --> 02:12:55,586
where we are headed

1309
02:13:19,276 --> 02:13:24,031
"I'm in love,
you are in love..."

1310
02:13:24,615 --> 02:13:28,619
so what have things come to be?

1311
02:13:29,620 --> 02:13:31,622
I am not unfaithful...

1312
02:13:32,039 --> 02:13:34,041
you are not unfaithful...

1313
02:13:34,625 --> 02:13:38,045
"so why do we hold
so much against each other?"

1314
02:13:40,005 --> 02:13:44,051
We were walking together...

1315
02:13:44,885 --> 02:13:49,056
"how have we come to be distanced
from each other?"

1316
02:13:54,645 --> 02:13:57,064
We don't even know...

1317
02:13:58,106 --> 02:14:01,068
where we will go

1318
02:14:23,465 --> 02:14:27,678
"My heart is immersed
in pain..."

1319
02:14:29,471 --> 02:14:32,683
my eyes are filled with tears

1320
02:14:33,976 --> 02:14:38,105
This season of loneliness...

1321
02:14:38,689 --> 02:14:42,109
isolates me from my path

1322
02:14:44,111 --> 02:14:48,115
"We had dreamt of achieving
our goal together"

1323
02:14:49,283 --> 02:14:53,704
But our paths are now different

1324
02:14:53,912 --> 02:14:58,125
Even as we walked together...

1325
02:14:58,375 --> 02:15:02,129
"I wonder how we
have lost our way"

1326
02:15:16,351 --> 02:15:20,731
"I'm in love,
you are in love..."

1327
02:15:21,064 --> 02:15:25,152
so what have things come to be?

1328
02:15:38,165 --> 02:15:41,168
Look at the lovebirds.
They're at it again

1329
02:15:41,752 --> 02:15:47,174
Their romance is beginning and Raj
and Priya's love is coming to an end

1330
02:15:47,758 --> 02:15:52,179
It's almost a month now.
- No one knows what caused the trouble

1331
02:15:52,262 --> 02:15:54,181
One moment. I'll explain

1332
02:15:54,431 --> 02:15:56,183
"Radha, come here"

1333
02:15:56,767 --> 02:16:00,437
Let's suppose Radha is Priya
and he's Raj

1334
02:16:00,771 --> 02:16:04,524
Now say something to each other.
Anything... get started

1335
02:16:06,109 --> 02:16:07,194
Go on

1336
02:16:07,778 --> 02:16:11,365
It's the man who starts it all.
- Why? It's the woman who starts it

1337
02:16:11,448 --> 02:16:14,201
"A woman speaks only when the man
does something wrong, isn't it?"

1338
02:16:14,534 --> 02:16:16,953
Are you telling me that it's the man
who's always at fault?

1339
02:16:17,120 --> 02:16:20,207
"Whatever, it's the man who
actually starts it all"

1340
02:16:20,290 --> 02:16:22,793
Won't the man react
when his wife keeps nagging him?

1341
02:16:22,959 --> 02:16:26,797
"Don't say anything against women, okay?
- Not against men either, okay?"

1342
02:16:27,089 --> 02:16:29,466
"Because you're a man, you've
got the power to scream at me?"

1343
02:16:29,591 --> 02:16:31,134
And who gave you the
power to scream at me?

1344
02:16:31,301 --> 02:16:33,804
"Enough, enough!
I get it"

1345
02:16:34,304 --> 02:16:36,223
Neither of them are at fault

1346
02:16:36,807 --> 02:16:38,809
They've separated for
no rhyme or reason

1347
02:16:40,811 --> 02:16:45,232
Wash the windshield properly.
It's the last time

1348
02:16:45,816 --> 02:16:49,820
So you've examined the truck?
Tell us if there is a problem

1349
02:16:51,822 --> 02:16:56,827
"Raj, think it over again
with a cool mind"

1350
02:16:57,119 --> 02:17:00,247
"You're not making a mistake by
selling off your trucks, are you?"

1351
02:17:02,124 --> 02:17:05,252
"I know I'm making a mistake, Manubhai.
- So why?"

1352
02:17:05,502 --> 02:17:09,256
I'm making a mistake.
But I have no other choice

1353
02:17:09,840 --> 02:17:12,843
"Unless I return Sameer's money,
I can't have any peace"

1354
02:17:23,353 --> 02:17:26,648
I wish to meet Mr Sameer Arora.
My name is Raj Mathur

1355
02:17:26,815 --> 02:17:29,359
"Mr Mathur, he's in a meeting
right now. Please be seated"

1356
02:17:30,068 --> 02:17:33,530
Tell him Raj Mathur is here.
It's urgent

1357
02:17:33,780 --> 02:17:36,533
"He's busy in a personal
meeting, Mr Mathur"

1358
02:17:36,658 --> 02:17:39,286
He has told us not to disturb
him for the next half hour

1359
02:17:39,369 --> 02:17:40,871
Please sit down

1360
02:18:35,925 --> 02:18:40,347
"When he's through with his personal
meeting, give him this cheque"

1361
02:18:47,604 --> 02:18:50,607
I'm telling you again.
Keep the cheque

1362
02:18:51,941 --> 02:18:55,362
"You can return it to me later.
- No, Sameer"

1363
02:18:55,945 --> 02:18:58,615
My work with the Australian
company has already begun

1364
02:18:59,240 --> 02:19:03,370
"I know that, Priya.
But I'm feeling very strange..."

1365
02:19:04,162 --> 02:19:06,706
the way you're returning
this cheque to me

1366
02:19:07,290 --> 02:19:09,959
"For me, it's very important to
return the cheque to you, Sameer"

1367
02:19:10,293 --> 02:19:14,381
"In fact, I shouldn't have
taken it from you at all"

1368
02:19:16,091 --> 02:19:20,970
"No, Priya. If a friend doesn't
help a friend, who will?"

1369
02:19:22,097 --> 02:19:26,393
"No, Sameer. It was my mistake"

1370
02:19:28,603 --> 02:19:32,982
"Before taking the money from you,
I should've considered..."

1371
02:19:34,192 --> 02:19:37,362
how much it would hurt Raj

1372
02:19:46,996 --> 02:19:51,418
If you think your relations with Raj
will be okay if I take back the money...

1373
02:19:51,668 --> 02:19:54,671
"I'll take it back.
- No, Sameer"

1374
02:19:55,588 --> 02:20:00,426
It isn't about money.
It's not money

1375
02:20:02,137 --> 02:20:08,434
"I admit, I made a mistake.
But what Raj said and did..."

1376
02:20:09,018 --> 02:20:13,439
no woman can ever tolerate.
She can't ever

1377
02:20:19,237 --> 02:20:23,449
"I had to relieve myself of a burden,
and I've done it"

1378
02:20:37,338 --> 02:20:39,382
Raj is such a fortunate man

1379
02:20:41,342 --> 02:20:43,178
You love him so much

1380
02:20:49,058 --> 02:20:54,480
"Let me drop you home.
- No, Sameer. I'll go on my own"

1381
02:21:05,074 --> 02:21:07,493
"I'm glad you're here, Manubhai.
- What happened?"

1382
02:21:07,619 --> 02:21:12,081
"Raj has been drinking all evening,
talking about Priya. Look"

1383
02:21:16,586 --> 02:21:19,088
Not a word from you.
I'll talk to him

1384
02:21:23,259 --> 02:21:26,888
"Raj, what's up?
Stop it now"

1385
02:21:27,096 --> 02:21:29,098
Let me drink this up

1386
02:21:29,182 --> 02:21:30,433
"What happened, Raj?"

1387
02:21:31,601 --> 02:21:36,522
All I want to ask Priya is:
Why did she go to Sameer?

1388
02:21:37,106 --> 02:21:40,109
"They're childhood friends,
we all know that"

1389
02:21:40,526 --> 02:21:45,782
"Raj, you aren't suggesting...?
- What rubbish! No!"

1390
02:21:46,574 --> 02:21:48,534
"I didn't mean that... no, not at all"

1391
02:21:48,618 --> 02:21:52,121
All I want to ask is why
she went to Sameer. That's it

1392
02:21:54,123 --> 02:21:57,126
"You're no longer together,
it could be anything else"

1393
02:21:57,210 --> 02:21:59,128
"What say, Manubhai?
- What anything else?"

1394
02:22:00,546 --> 02:22:04,550
What if she's not with me?
She's still my wife and I...

1395
02:22:05,343 --> 02:22:09,138
"Why're you getting sentimental?
- Yes, I'm sentimental!"

1396
02:22:10,139 --> 02:22:13,559
"And she knows that too and
despite that, she went there"

1397
02:22:21,484 --> 02:22:24,153
I'll be back in a moment.
- Where to?

1398
02:22:24,487 --> 02:22:27,782
I'll just go and ask Priya
why she went to Sameer

1399
02:22:27,865 --> 02:22:29,158
Listen...

1400
02:22:30,493 --> 02:22:34,705
"You think I'm going to fight with her?
Bansi, get us some more drinks"

1401
02:22:35,164 --> 02:22:38,167
"If I had to fight, I'd have
given Sameer a punch right there"

1402
02:22:39,168 --> 02:22:41,921
I'm only going to ask her.
Only to ask her

1403
02:22:42,839 --> 02:22:44,966
Go ahead and drink.
I'll be back

1404
02:22:47,176 --> 02:22:48,594
"No, I don't want the car"

1405
02:22:48,719 --> 02:22:51,180
Theirs is a strange love.
I can't understand it

1406
02:22:52,890 --> 02:22:55,935
I think there's going to be a fight

1407
02:22:56,978 --> 02:22:59,689
But I also get the feeling that...

1408
02:23:00,064 --> 02:23:04,610
"since he's meeting her after
many days, they'll get cozy"

1409
02:23:04,986 --> 02:23:07,196
lt'll all be settled.
Take it from me

1410
02:23:07,530 --> 02:23:09,740
"Bansi, get us some glasses"

1411
02:23:19,500 --> 02:23:22,378
"Madam, one Raj Mathur
is here to meet you"

1412
02:23:22,753 --> 02:23:27,300
Raj Mathur? At this hour?
Ask him to come tomorrow morning

1413
02:23:27,633 --> 02:23:30,219
"Tomorrow morning? Okay, madam...
- Tomorrow morning, my foot!"

1414
02:23:30,553 --> 02:23:32,221
Give me the phone

1415
02:23:33,973 --> 02:23:37,476
"Aunt, it's Raj.
I want to have a word with Priya"

1416
02:23:37,852 --> 02:23:40,980
You can't meet her at this hour.
Is this any time for decent folks?

1417
02:23:41,314 --> 02:23:46,235
What decent folks? I want to talk
to my wife. Please give her the phone

1418
02:23:47,862 --> 02:23:50,323
I told you once.
You can't meet her. That's it

1419
02:23:50,656 --> 02:23:51,908
What's once...?

1420
02:23:53,242 --> 02:23:55,036
She hung up on me!

1421
02:23:55,620 --> 02:23:57,914
I don't need anyone's permission
to meet my wife!

1422
02:23:58,247 --> 02:24:00,708
"What are you doing, sir?
- Please leave"

1423
02:24:01,042 --> 02:24:03,002
I want to see my wife

1424
02:24:17,058 --> 02:24:18,726
"Guard, don't let him get in"

1425
02:24:18,935 --> 02:24:22,229
Will I have to take your permission
to meet my wife?

1426
02:24:22,563 --> 02:24:25,066
We have so many problems
only because of you!

1427
02:24:26,025 --> 02:24:27,693
Don't talk like a thug

1428
02:24:27,902 --> 02:24:29,528
You call me a thug!

1429
02:24:29,779 --> 02:24:30,947
"Yes, you're a thug"

1430
02:24:31,280 --> 02:24:33,950
"You're a thug, a ruffian!
- Get the hell out of here!"

1431
02:24:34,283 --> 02:24:35,993
Why're you pushing me?

1432
02:24:36,285 --> 02:24:39,372
What drama is this? Stop it!
Let us sleep!

1433
02:24:39,705 --> 02:24:42,083
Go inside and sleep!
- Stop this drama

1434
02:24:42,416 --> 02:24:44,418
Decent folks live here.
- You're decent...

1435
02:24:44,752 --> 02:24:48,089
"because you live in tall buildings?
She calls me a thug, a ruffian!"

1436
02:24:48,422 --> 02:24:50,633
I'm going to beat her up!

1437
02:24:51,092 --> 02:24:52,426
Stop pushing me

1438
02:24:55,471 --> 02:24:57,723
What's the matter?
What racket is this?

1439
02:24:58,099 --> 02:25:00,768
"It's your son-in-law, the thug.
He's showing his true colours"

1440
02:25:01,102 --> 02:25:02,645
Leave me alone!

1441
02:25:29,338 --> 02:25:32,466
I'll tell the police you are
not letting me meet my wife

1442
02:25:32,800 --> 02:25:34,927
Even the police have arrived!

1443
02:25:35,344 --> 02:25:37,680
Let go of my hand!
I'll report you guys

1444
02:25:38,139 --> 02:25:39,807
Let go of him. Leave him alone.
- Sir...

1445
02:25:40,141 --> 02:25:42,143
I want to meet my wife.
- You get drunk and cause trouble?

1446
02:25:42,351 --> 02:25:43,352
No

1447
02:25:43,602 --> 02:25:45,604
Say whatever you want to
at the police station

1448
02:25:49,108 --> 02:25:52,820
"What are you doing, sir...?
I want to meet my wife"

1449
02:25:53,154 --> 02:25:53,821
Hold it

1450
02:25:56,031 --> 02:25:57,658
Please let him go

1451
02:26:00,244 --> 02:26:01,996
He's my husband

1452
02:26:03,164 --> 02:26:05,791
Your husband?
- Yes

1453
02:26:08,502 --> 02:26:12,173
"All right. I'll let him go,
because you're asking me to"

1454
02:26:13,090 --> 02:26:15,718
You are educated and decent folks

1455
02:26:16,093 --> 02:26:19,013
Does it look nice to publicly
behave like a thug?

1456
02:26:19,346 --> 02:26:21,640
Get in... go on
Get on with your work

1457
02:26:22,141 --> 02:26:24,935
It's a husband-wife quarrel.
Go on

1458
02:26:56,217 --> 02:26:58,219
"Go home, Raj. Please"

1459
02:27:01,347 --> 02:27:03,766
"You've made a mockery
of our marriage, Raj"

1460
02:27:04,558 --> 02:27:08,103
It wasn't my intention
to do that

1461
02:27:09,146 --> 02:27:13,067
All I came to ask you was...

1462
02:27:13,442 --> 02:27:16,779
"and they stopped me.
Called me a thug, a ruffian"

1463
02:27:18,656 --> 02:27:21,617
"I don't know why it happened.
- It happens all the time, Raj?"

1464
02:27:22,493 --> 02:27:26,914
All the time?
In Sameer's presence the other day...

1465
02:27:27,331 --> 02:27:31,460
"and now, in the presence
of the whole world? Why?"

1466
02:27:32,544 --> 02:27:36,173
Have you ever thought
what I'm going through?

1467
02:27:39,260 --> 02:27:42,888
"I try to do one thing, but I always
end up doing something else"

1468
02:27:44,348 --> 02:27:48,644
"I know that.
I know you very well, Raj"

1469
02:27:49,520 --> 02:27:52,606
But I can't take it anymore.
I can't

1470
02:27:55,275 --> 02:27:58,821
Rather than live together
and hurt each other...

1471
02:28:00,197 --> 02:28:02,032
we'd better separate

1472
02:28:04,284 --> 02:28:06,495
"Don't say that, Priya"

1473
02:28:07,287 --> 02:28:10,624
"Remember what you once told me, Raj?"

1474
02:28:13,293 --> 02:28:16,839
"In the world somewhere,
there will be someone very happy..."

1475
02:28:17,506 --> 02:28:20,509
because you are happy
Remember?

1476
02:28:24,304 --> 02:28:26,807
Go on. Go home

1477
02:29:09,433 --> 02:29:15,272
"My child, think again.
It's a very crucial step"

1478
02:29:15,647 --> 02:29:18,233
And you can't take such decisions
in haste

1479
02:29:18,567 --> 02:29:21,028
"Kishore, what's gotten into you?"

1480
02:29:21,361 --> 02:29:24,364
If Priya has decided to leave India
and go away to Greece...

1481
02:29:24,698 --> 02:29:27,159
she must've thought about it

1482
02:29:27,493 --> 02:29:30,829
You saw the racket
he created last night

1483
02:29:31,288 --> 02:29:32,372
Priya...?

1484
02:29:36,376 --> 02:29:39,588
It's very difficult for me
to live with Raj

1485
02:29:41,590 --> 02:29:46,845
And it's also difficult for me
to live here and stay away from him

1486
02:30:02,319 --> 02:30:04,321
"What have I gone
and done, Manubhai?"

1487
02:30:05,405 --> 02:30:08,742
What did I set out to do...?
And what did I end up doing!

1488
02:30:09,076 --> 02:30:14,039
That's the trouble with you!
You think after you do!

1489
02:30:17,709 --> 02:30:21,213
What am I to do now?

1490
02:30:21,630 --> 02:30:24,967
What can you do?
You've done what you had to!

1491
02:30:25,300 --> 02:30:28,553
So why're you asking us
what to do? Why ask us!

1492
02:30:28,929 --> 02:30:32,641
After doing everything...
- Calm down

1493
02:30:37,604 --> 02:30:41,191
"Son, let's go home"

1494
02:30:41,775 --> 02:30:45,112
"No, I'm not going home"

1495
02:30:45,529 --> 02:30:46,780
Hear that?

1496
02:30:48,448 --> 02:30:50,450
I feel very lonely there

1497
02:30:52,452 --> 02:30:57,666
Tell me... what should I do?
I don't want to lose her

1498
02:30:59,751 --> 02:31:03,338
"Raj, Priya called to say she's
going away to Greece forever"

1499
02:31:03,672 --> 02:31:06,675
She has left for the airport.
The flight leaves at 10:30

1500
02:31:07,551 --> 02:31:10,470
Hear that? What are you
going to do now?

1501
02:31:10,804 --> 02:31:12,681
She's leaving!

1502
02:31:13,390 --> 02:31:15,934
"No, I won't let her go"

1503
02:31:17,227 --> 02:31:19,187
I'm not letting Priya go away

1504
02:32:15,535 --> 02:32:17,287
Where's Priya?
- She has left

1505
02:32:17,621 --> 02:32:19,331
Where?
- She's in there

1506
02:32:19,539 --> 02:32:22,167
"Where to? Where's your ticket?
- Mister, I've got to in"

1507
02:32:22,542 --> 02:32:25,295
"He's not going abroad,
he's going to meet his wife"

1508
02:32:25,629 --> 02:32:27,088
That's not allowed

1509
02:32:29,758 --> 02:32:31,551
Mr Tiwari...
- What happened?

1510
02:32:31,885 --> 02:32:33,887
Priya's going away.
- Where to?

1511
02:32:34,262 --> 02:32:35,931
She's leaving me and going away.
- Don't tell me!

1512
02:32:36,181 --> 02:32:39,226
I've got to stop her. Please ask him
to let me go in for five minutes

1513
02:32:39,559 --> 02:32:41,436
Let me talk to him

1514
02:32:41,770 --> 02:32:43,563
"Listen, Yadav"

1515
02:32:49,486 --> 02:32:52,113
"Go on, Raj. Hurry up.
- Just 15 minutes"

1516
02:32:53,573 --> 02:32:56,451
Where are you going...?
- One moment

1517
02:32:56,785 --> 02:32:59,120
Listen...

1518
02:33:03,792 --> 02:33:05,126
Hurry!

1519
02:34:55,695 --> 02:34:56,905
Don't go

1520
02:34:58,031 --> 02:35:01,910
I know I've made a mistake.
Please forgive me

1521
02:35:05,789 --> 02:35:10,168
"Raj, that's just what I was trying
to explain to you last night"

1522
02:35:11,711 --> 02:35:14,506
Rather than live together
and hurt each other...

1523
02:35:14,923 --> 02:35:16,508
we'd better part

1524
02:35:18,843 --> 02:35:21,721
Whether you take the decision
to separate or I...

1525
02:35:22,055 --> 02:35:25,934
"isn't it one and the same thing?
- No, Priya"

1526
02:35:27,644 --> 02:35:29,646
"I know, I'm the one
who has made a mistake"

1527
02:35:30,939 --> 02:35:34,275
But give me one more chance.
Please Priya

1528
02:35:36,277 --> 02:35:38,154
"Can you be happy without me, Priya?"

1529
02:35:41,741 --> 02:35:43,618
"Maybe not, Raj"

1530
02:35:44,953 --> 02:35:48,289
But it isn't necessary to have
the company of someone you love...

1531
02:35:49,082 --> 02:35:51,167
"for a lifetime, is it?"

1532
02:35:58,758 --> 02:36:02,971
"How many times will you say that, Raj?
How many times?"

1533
02:36:04,973 --> 02:36:08,810
"Don't make it any more difficult
for me to go away, Raj. Please don't"

1534
02:36:11,938 --> 02:36:14,983
Maybe this is what was
to come out of our marriage

1535
02:36:24,200 --> 02:36:27,328
"No, Priya. This isn't
the outcome of our marriage"

1536
02:36:34,002 --> 02:36:37,005
"Priya, I've had a dream"

1537
02:36:39,007 --> 02:36:44,012
We have two children.
A son and a daughter

1538
02:36:45,930 --> 02:36:48,016
The son is just like you

1539
02:36:49,017 --> 02:36:53,146
He only has a nose like mine

1540
02:36:58,026 --> 02:37:02,113
The daughter is very pretty.
She has your eyes...

1541
02:37:02,905 --> 02:37:06,326
she's very nice too. Like you

1542
02:37:12,165 --> 02:37:14,208
"You're a very nice person, Priya"

1543
02:37:15,835 --> 02:37:18,463
"I could've changed for the
better too, in your company"

1544
02:37:19,756 --> 02:37:22,342
"Don't go away, Priya.
I'll change my ways..."

1545
02:37:23,843 --> 02:37:27,055
"I'm sorry, Aunt Anna"

1546
02:37:32,518 --> 02:37:35,772
I'll even say sorry to Sameer

1547
02:37:38,066 --> 02:37:41,736
"When the children wake up at night,
I'll look after them"

1548
02:37:42,070 --> 02:37:46,657
"I won't give you any trouble.
Please don't go away, Priya"

1549
02:37:48,076 --> 02:37:51,871
"If you go away,
it'll shatter my dream"

1550
02:37:54,791 --> 02:38:01,547
"Raj, I've had the same dreams.
The same dreams, Raj"

1551
02:38:05,885 --> 02:38:08,388
But reality is otherwise

1552
02:38:15,186 --> 02:38:18,106
O beloved...

1553
02:39:07,071 --> 02:39:11,367
"My loneliness, the ache
in my heart, never went away"

1554
02:39:11,951 --> 02:39:14,620
"The whole world
pokes at fun"

1555
02:39:18,082 --> 02:39:21,586
"You and I break up, my love..."

1556
02:39:22,962 --> 02:39:25,965
"like a star breaking away
from the skies"

1557
02:40:22,146 --> 02:40:24,899
"God, if I'm no more..."

1558
02:40:26,025 --> 02:40:28,027
look after Priya

1559
02:40:29,236 --> 02:40:34,492
Because I love Priya
very very much

1560
02:40:49,382 --> 02:40:54,261
"You are bidding me a farewell
and leaving me in God's care"

1561
02:40:55,012 --> 02:41:00,267
But you have broken my heart

1562
02:41:05,064 --> 02:41:08,609
"Broken hearts
are never put together again"

1563
02:41:11,070 --> 02:41:14,740
"You and I breaking up, my love..."

1564
02:41:16,283 --> 02:41:20,287
"like a star breaking away
from the skies"

1565
02:42:02,037 --> 02:42:05,332
"How often have I told you to keep
your shoes at the right place, Raj?"

1566
02:42:28,230 --> 02:42:31,358
"I couldn't go away, Raj.
I couldn't"

1567
02:42:35,654 --> 02:42:39,617
I can't live without you

1568
02:42:40,534 --> 02:42:47,541
"I realise, Raj, that I belong here.
In this house. With you"

1569
02:42:50,169 --> 02:42:54,882
And this talisman belongs
with you

1570
02:43:01,096 --> 02:43:04,642
"The dreams we saw
were the same, Raj"

1571
02:43:06,268 --> 02:43:09,480
And we can fulfill them
only by living together

1572
02:43:45,182 --> 02:43:48,560
"Promise me, Priya.
You will not leave me ever again"

1573
02:43:49,144 --> 02:43:51,271
And you must promise
never to shout at me again

1574
02:43:51,605 --> 02:43:54,108
"When do I...?
All right, I won't"

1575
02:43:54,441 --> 02:43:58,112
But why did you leave me and go away?
- You said such nasty things to me

1576
02:43:58,445 --> 02:44:01,699
"I know, but I went to Aunt Anna's
house to bring you back"

1577
02:44:02,074 --> 02:44:04,952
"Not to bring me back, to fight with me.
- That's what Aunt Anna says"

1578
02:44:05,577 --> 02:44:08,122
That's it! You get wrong
things in your mind!

1579
02:44:08,455 --> 02:44:10,249
I know what's on your mind right now!
- What?

1580
02:44:10,582 --> 02:44:12,584
When I'm picking up the shoes.
- No...

1581
02:44:13,502 --> 02:44:16,922
"All right, but did I say anything?
- No, but I understand"

1582
02:44:17,256 --> 02:44:19,133
This is love.
- This isn't love

1583
02:44:19,466 --> 02:44:22,010
"Shoes are where shoes should be,
and love is where love is"

1584
02:44:22,344 --> 02:44:25,806
So my love is a shoe?
- That's not what I said

1585
02:44:26,473 --> 02:44:27,808
Don't shout at me.
- Am I shouting?

1586
02:44:28,100 --> 02:44:31,270
You promised you wouldn't shout.
- But I shout to show my love

1587
02:44:31,603 --> 02:44:34,273
That's your way of showing love?
- Yes

1588
02:44:36,483 --> 02:44:38,485
"Shut up, will you?
We're making love"

